        "text": "1 Kings 1:45",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc.), for their brethren had prepared them for them. The object of הכינוּ, sc. the eating and drinking, may easily be supplied from the context. אחיהם are the inhabitants of Hebron and the neighbourhood; the tribe of Judah in general, who had already recognised David as king.",
